# A stuff programming example



#---------------------------------------------------------
	new (2)
#---------------------------------------------------------
# here we created an empty stack
# the parentheses mean: `do this first`, i use them for readability
# you can also write this command as: 2 [] stack
# it`s because first you have to put the reuired arguments on the main
# stack, so, we put the name of the new stack and it`s default value
#---------------------------------------------------------


#---------------------------------------------------------
	def main
#---------------------------------------------------------
# this is where the program begins, you use : to define a word, a word
# is like a function in other languages
#---------------------------------------------------------


#---------------------------------------------------------
	select (2)
#---------------------------------------------------------
# here we select our new stack, use "select (main)" to go back
#---------------------------------------------------------


#---------------------------------------------------------
	emit ("hello world" ASC LEN)
#---------------------------------------------------------
# here we first put the ASCII value of the string "hello world" on the
# stack using the ASC command, we need to do that because strings on the
# program are stored in a temporary buffer since the stack can only
# handle numbers. So, after doing that we then used LEN, since our string
# is still on the buffer we can still do things with it, so we used LEN
# to get the string`s length, we did that because EMIT takes two arguments
# 1 -> the string(in ascii); 2 -> the string`s size.
#---------------------------------------------------------


#---------------------------------------------------------
	CB
#---------------------------------------------------------
# CB(clear buffer), clears the string buffer
#---------------------------------------------------------

	
#---------------------------------------------------------
	endef
#---------------------------------------------------------
# this ends the word/function definition
#---------------------------------------------------------
